extendedInfo.description: First Security Bank of MissoulaTo access mobile banking you must be a First Security Bank of Missoula Online Banking customer. To sign up for Online Banking and receive access to mobile banking using your mobile device, customers can enroll by visiting the banks website and using the APPLY NOW drop down.  Sign up for mobile banking through your new Online Banking account.  Click on the Options tab, click the mobile settings tab and activate mobile banking access.  Then, begin browsing on your phone using the app just installed.  Our mobile banking is a solution that enables bank customers to use their Android to initiate routine transactions and conduct research anytime, from anywhere.  Customers can view account balances and transaction history, view account alerts, initiate account transfers and pay bills. First Security Bank of Missoula Mobile Banking supports all account types including checking, savings, money market, certificates of deposit, loans and line of credit.First Security Bank of Missoula Mobile Banking is a FREE* service that allows you to access your account anytime, from anywhere, using your Android.*There is no fee from First Security Bank of Missoula.  Connectivity and usage rates may apply.  Contact your wireless service provider for more details.First Security Bank of Missoula - Member FDIC

reviews.title: Won\'t log in

reviews.title: Update...great customer service!

Apparently you need to modify text alerts and mobile settings from the web browser log in before using the app.  ORIGINAL POST: Keep getting the following message when app asks me to set up text messaging alerts when first logging in:   System Response Error.
